FRUIT-FILLED OATMEAL BARS

1 1/2 c all-purpose flour		1/2 tsp baking soda
1 1/2 c quick-cooking rolled oats	3/4 c butter or margarine
1 c packed brown sugar

Stir together flour, oats, brown sugar, and baking soda.  Cut in
butter until mixture is crumbly.  Pat 2/3 of the crumbs into the
bottom of an ungreased 13x9x2 baking pan.  Spread with filling.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.  Bake at 375 for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.  Cut into bars.

FILLINGS:
Apricot -- use 1 c apricot preserves.
Raisin -- 
1/4 c granulated sugar		2 c raisins
1 Tbsp cornstarch		1 c water

Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.  Stir in raisins and water.
Cook and stir until bubbly.

Prune --
1 c snipped, pitted prunes			1/2 c packed brown sugar
2/3 c water					1/2 c chopped walnuts
1/2 of a 6-oz can lemonade concentrate		2 Tbsp all-purpose flour

Combine prunes, water, and lemonade concentrate in a saucepan.  Cover
and simmer for 5 minutes.  In a bowl, mix the brown sugaar, walnuts,
and flour.  Stir into prune mixutre.  Cook and stir until very thick.










